thods=[\'GET\'])\\ndef get_match_data(match_id):\\n    match_data = MatchData.query.get_or_404(match_id)\\n    return jsonify(match_data.to_dict()), 200\\n\\n@app.route(\'/analyze_performance/<int:match_id>\', methods=[\'GET\'])\\ndef analyze_performance(match_id):\\n    match_data = MatchData.query.get_or_404(match_id)\\n    performance = match_data.player_performance\\n    # Placeholder for performance analysis logic\\n    return jsonify({\'performance_analysis\': performance}), 200\\n\\nif __name__ == \'__main__\':\\n    create_tables()\\n    app.run(debug=True)\\n"\n}\n```\n\nThis `solution.py` file sets up a basic Flask application with SQLAlchemy for database management and CORS for cross-origin resource sharing. It includes routes for uploading match data, retrieving match data, and analyzing player performance. The `MatchData` model is used to store match details and player performance data in a SQLite database.', role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)
